        {
            "id" : "7be10922",
            "text" : [ "<span class=\"smGameTextTitleSize\">In this level, we will explore:</span><p class=\"smGameTextSize\">The pursuit of an indisputable truth, which may actually be imprecise in reality.</p>", "<p class=\"smGameTextSize\">How an answer with a degree of uncertainty can be more accurate than a previously accepted 'truth.'</p>" ],
            "desc": null,
            "next" : "8b7f00aa",
            "prev" : null,
            "jumpTo" : null,
            "answer": 0,
            "score" : 1,
            "position": "center"
        },
        {
            "id" : "8b7f00aa",
            "text" : [ "<span class=\"smGameTextTitleSize\">Iberian Discovery</span><p class=\"smGameTextSize\">On <span class=\"htdate\"></span>, Christopher Columbus wrote a letter to the king reporting his arrival in the <i>\"Indies\"</i> (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillPrimarySource('6bffd681-8f79-4773-914b-45fcc09bb6a2'); return false;\">Christopher Columbus, <span class=\"htdate\"></span>, pp. 184 - 186</a>).", "<p class=\"smGameTextSize\">Fray Bartolomé de las Casas, when referring to the discovery, stated that God gave Columbus <i>'the keys to open the sea and discover new lands'</i> (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('daaaf7ba-7319-463b-a30b-55b14dbbad94'); return false;\">Casas, Bartolomé de las F, <span class=\"htdate\"></span>, pp. 471</a>)</p>" ],
            "desc": null,
            "next" : "8e419a6f",
            "prev" : "7be10922",
            "jumpTo" : null,
            "answer": 0,
            "score" : 1,
            "position": "center"
        },
        {
            "id" : "8b7f00aa",
            "text" : [ "<span class=\"smGameTextTitleSize\">Iberian Discovery</span><p class=\"smGameTextSize\">There are also controversies regarding who first sighted the new continent during a voyage sponsored by the Spanish monarchs: Was it Rodrigo de Triana, Juan Rodríguez Bermejo, or Christopher Columbus? (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('43ab9622-2e48-48da-926e-688229fc8b11'); return false;\">Jesús Varela Marcos, Real Academia de la História </a> ; <a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('ac201e1f-39de-48df-9627-7df9aed62dd4'); return false;\">Biblioteca Virtual Miguel de Cervantes</a>).</p>" ],
            "desc": null,
            "next" : "1318af79",
            "prev" : "8b7f00aa",
            "jumpTo" : null,
            "answer": 0,
            "score" : 1,
            "position": "center"
        },
        {
            "id" : "1318af79",
            "text" : [ "<span class=\"smGameTextTitleSize\">Iberian Discovery</span><p class=\"desc\"><img id=\"imgBRES140\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgBRES140', '0%')\" style=\"width: 25%;\" class=\"imgcenter\" src=\"images/Archive/BRes140146_0206.jpg\" /><b>Figure 1</b>: Excerpt from Christopher Columbus's letter reporting the discovery (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillPrimarySource('6bffd681-8f79-4773-914b-45fcc09bb6a2'); return false;\">Colon, Cristóbal , <span class=\"htdate\"></span>, pp. 185</a>).</p>" ],
            "desc": null,
            "next" : "8e419a6f",
            "prev" : "8b7f00aa",
            "jumpTo" : null,
            "answer": 0,
            "score" : 1,
            "position": "top"
        },
        {
            "id" : "715cbd75",
            "text" : [ "<span class=\"smGameTextTitleSize\">Nordic Discovery</span><p class=\"smGameTextSize\">In the Saga of Erik the Red, we learn that his son, Leif, arrived in <i>\"Vinland\"</i>, a region now identified as part of the American (<i>Abya Ayala</i>) continent (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('45d5b35c-5f81-46e5-b666-c4a6e257a28d'); return false;\">Septhon, J., <span class=\"htdate\"></span>, pp. 15, 16</a> ; <a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('8f31ba39-e450-4654-b4cf-c01e5793eb5f'); return false;\">Septhon, J., <span class=\"htdate\"></span>, Chapter 5</a>; <a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('8b15e438-93b6-4ae1-ab5b-7e150abcbf30'); return false;\">Wallace, B., <span class=\"htdate\"></span></a>).</p>" ],
            "desc": null,
            "next" : "e857bcf5",
            "prev" : "8b7f00aa",
            "jumpTo" : null,
            "answer": 0,
            "score" : 1,
            "position": "center"
        },
        {
            "id" : "e857bcf5",
            "text" : [ "<span class=\"smGameTextTitleSize\">Nordic Discovery</span><p class=\"smGameTextSize\">The Saga of the Greenlanders also mentions <i>\"Vinland\"</i>, but it provides different information, which is likely more accurate: Bjarni Herjolfsson is credited as the first to discover <i>\"Vinland\"</i> (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('db596dfb-03b5-46c5-8cbf-446614462c91'); return false;\">Grænlendinga saga</a> ; <a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('c63c9082-4a2f-40bf-962f-6db0b8703253'); return false;\">JÓHANNESSON, J., & Oleson, T. J., <span class=\"htdate\"></span> </a>; <a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('8b15e438-93b6-4ae1-ab5b-7e150abcbf30'); return false;\">Wallace, B., <span class=\"htdate\"></span></a>).</p>" ],
            "desc": null,
            "next" : "a74a8846",
            "prev" : "715cbd75",
            "jumpTo" : null,
            "answer": 0,
            "score" : 1,
            "position": "center"
        },
        {
            "id" : "a74a8846",
            "text" : [ "<p class=\"smGameTextSize\">We need to define the hypotheses, which are the possible answers to be tested:</p>", "<p class=\"smGameTextSize\"><b>HYPOTHESIS 1</b>: The Spanish expedition was responsible for discovering America (<i>Abya Ayala</i>) (a new route to the \"Indies\").</p>", "<p class=\"smGameTextSize\"><b>HYPOTHESIS 2</b>: The Norse were the first to discover America (<i>\"Vinland\"</i>).</p>", "<p class=\"smGameTextSize\"><b>HYPOTHESIS 3</b>: Although we do not know the person's name, the first to reach America (<i>Abya Ayala</i>) was not European.</p>", "<p class=\"smGameTextSize\"><b>HYPOTHESIS 4</b>: The continent was discovered by different groups of people.</p>" ],
            "desc": null,
            "next" : "0bf8dcaa",
            "prev" : "e857bcf5",
            "jumpTo" : null,
            "answer": 0,
            "score" : 1,
            "position": "center"
        },
        {
            "id" : "0bf8dcaa",
            "text" : [ "<span class=\"smGameTextTitleSize\">Validating HYPOTHESIS 1 (1/2)</span><p class=\"smGameTextSize\">In addition to Columbus's letters and accounts mentioning Rodrigo de Triana (Juan Rodríguez Bermejo) (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillPrimarySource('6bffd681-8f79-4773-914b-45fcc09bb6a2'); return false;\">Christopher Columbus, <span class=\"htdate\"></span>, pp. 184 - 186</a> ; <a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('ac201e1f-39de-48df-9627-7df9aed62dd4'); return false;\">Biblioteca Virtual Miguel de Cervantes</a>), we also know that the expedition brought several items back to Spain (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('daaaf7ba-7319-463b-a30b-55b14dbbad94'); return false;\">Casas, Bartolomé de las F, <span class=\"htdate\"></span>, pp. 477</a>):</p>", "<p class=\"smGameTextSize\"><ul><li>Seven \"Indians\" who survived the journey</li><li>A beautiful green parrot</li><li><b>Many other things never before seen or heard of in Spain</b></li></ul></p>", "<p class=\"smGameTextSize\"><div class=\"first_steps_reflection_parent\"><div class=\"first_steps_reflection smGameTextSize\"><b>Regarding the Evidence:</b><br />Could these previously unseen objects help prove the success of the voyage?</div></div></p>" ],
            "desc": [ "The only witnesses to the journey were those who traveled together. Therefore, bringing back animals, unfamiliar objects, and natives—although a questionable practice—was an effective way to demonstrate the success of the expedition." ],
            "next" : "bda5c60b",
            "prev" : null,
            "jumpTo" : null,
            "answer": 1,
            "score" : 2,
            "position": "top"
        },
        {
            "id" : "bda5c60b",
            "text" : [ "<span class=\"smGameTextTitleSize\">Validating HYPOTHESIS 1 (2/2)</span><p class=\"smGameTextSize\">Christopher Columbus's letters mention 'Indians', and he also brought some of them to Spain (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillPrimarySource('6bffd681-8f79-4773-914b-45fcc09bb6a2'); return false;\">Christopher Columbus, <span class=\"htdate\"></span>, pp. 184 - 186</a> ; <a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('daaaf7ba-7319-463b-a30b-55b14dbbad94'); return false;\">Casas, Bartolomé de las F, <span class=\"htdate\"></span>, pp. 477</a>). Considering this, we need to reflect:</p>", "<p class=\"smGameTextSize\"><div class=\"first_steps_reflection_parent\"><div class=\"first_steps_reflection smGameTextSize\"><b>On Rigorousness</b><br />Do these events indicate that people were already living on the American (<i>Abya Ayala</i>) continent before the Europeans arrived?</div></div></p>" ],
            "desc": [ "Columbus's description shows that he expected to reach the 'Indies' and, therefore, anticipated encountering inhabitants. He set sail from Spain with the belief that he would discover a new route to a land with established populations. However, he arrived on an unknown continent, encountering people unfamiliar to him." ],
            "next" : "0e196bd9",
            "prev" : null,
            "jumpTo" : null,
            "answer": 1,
            "score" : 2,
            "position": "top"
        },
        {
            "id" : "0e196bd9",
            "text" : [ "<span class=\"smGameTextTitleSize\">Validating HYPOTHESIS 2 (1/2)</span><p class=\"smGameTextSize\">The chronicles mention the arrival of Norse people in \"Vinland\", a fact indirectly confirmed by the archaeological site at L’Anse aux Meadows (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('43acd80b-d8f6-482e-a251-139661d9c1ec'); return false;\">Birgitta, Wallace, <span class=\"htdate\"></span></a>)</p>", "<p class=\"desc\"><img id=\"imgLAMSE\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgLAMSE', '0%')\" class=\"imgcenter\" src=\"images/UNESCO/Lanse.jpg\" /><b>Figure 1</b>:  Archaeological National Site of L'Anse aux Meadows. Photo by Dick Houghton, available on the UNESCO website (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('35411d10-e127-42ab-b1c9-13b4461e4ea8'); return false;\">UNESCO, <span class=\"htdate\"></span></a>). Shared under license <a href=\"https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/2.0/deed.en\" target=\"_blank\">Attribution-Noncommercial 2.0 Generic</a>.</p>" ],
            "desc": null,
            "next" : "3efdf99e",
            "prev" : null,
            "jumpTo" : null,
            "answer": 0,
            "score" : 1,
            "position": "top"
        },
        {
            "id" : "3efdf99e",
            "text" : [ "<span class=\"smGameTextTitleSize\">Validating HYPOTHESIS 2 (2/2)</span><p class=\"smGameTextSize\">Robert McGhee compares the sagas with evidence found in Canada and also notes the presence of indigenous people in the region when the Norse arrived (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('88294169-d7c1-4c98-9e73-a324470cd808'); return false;\">McGhee, Robert, <span class=\"htdate\"></span> </a>).</p>", "<p class=\"smGameTextSize\"><div class=\"first_steps_reflection_parent\"><div class=\"first_steps_reflection smGameTextSize\"><div class=\"first_steps_reflection question_mark\">?</div><div class=\"first_steps_reflection\"><b>Indirect evidences</b><br />Can an archaeological site and objects confirm the Norse presence?</div></div></p>" ],
            "desc": "When direct evidence is unavailable, often due to natural deterioration, the existence of a site can be proven through objects contemporary to the people described in the sagas. The archaeological site at L'Anse aux Meadows provides substantial indirect evidence to support this.",
            "next" : "1e01e7f6",
            "prev" : null,
            "jumpTo" : null,
            "answer": 1,
            "score" : 2,
            "position": "top"
        },
        {
            "id" : "1e01e7f6",
            "text" : [ "<span class=\"smGameTextTitleSize\">Validating HYPOTHESIS 3 (1/8)</span><p class=\"smGameTextSize\">In addition to references to indigenous people as 'Indians,' the presence of humans in the Americas (<i>Abya Ayala</i>) can be confirmed through various archaeological sites, such as the sacred city of Caral in Peru, which dates back approximately 5,000 years (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('720f6dfd-4b86-4e07-a887-1010e1041a4d'); return false;\">Ruta Caral, <span class=\"htdate\"></span></a> ; <a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('03c3743c-d268-4730-ba8e-d36b5c49e781'); return false;\">Youtube - Caral Perú Oficial, <span class=\"htdate\"></span></a> ; <a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('a7abe0b7-b3bf-44d6-ab4d-e7d32d2586ad'); return false;\">Moras, Roberto., <span class=\"htdate\"></span></a> ; <a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('d76a60c6-1eaa-4e1e-9b72-2135509101c1'); return false;\">Legado Ancestral, <span class=\"htdate\"></span>, Caral parte 2 - Tecnología en el año 4.000 A.C.</a>):</p>", "<p class=\"desc\"><img id=\"imgCaral\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgCaral', '0%')\" src=\"images/Caral/CaralPiramideH1.jpg\" class=\"imgcenter\"/><b>Figure 2</b>: Photo of Pyramid H1 at the archaeological site of Caral (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('720f6dfd-4b86-4e07-a887-1010e1041a4d'); return false;\">Ruta Caral, <span class=\"htdate\"></span></a> ; <a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('03c3743c-d268-4730-ba8e-d36b5c49e781'); return false;\">Youtube - Caral Perú Oficial, <span class=\"htdate\"></span></a>). Photo taken on <span class=\"htdate\"></span>, during a visit to the site.</p>" ],
            "desc": null,
            "next" : "920a393a",
            "prev" : null,
            "jumpTo" : null,
            "answer": 1,
            "score" : 1,
            "position": "top"
        },
        {
            "id" : "920a393a",
            "text" : [ "<span class=\"smGameTextTitleSize\">Validating HYPOTHESIS 3 (2/8)</span><p class=\"smGameTextSize\">In Costa Rica, various indigenous artifacts from different parts of the Americas (<i>Abya Ayala</i>) suggest contact between different indigenous groups:</p>", "<p class=\"desc\"><img id=\"imgMayaCRJade\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgMayaCRJade', '0%')\" src=\"images/SanJoseCRJade/MayaCRJade.jpg\" style=\"width: 25%;\" class=\"imgcenter\"/><b>Figure 3</b>: Maya inscription at the Museo del Jade in San José, Costa Rica. Photo taken on <span class=\"htdate\"></span>, during a visit to the museum.</p>" ],
            "desc": null,
            "next" : "c44552ad",
            "prev" : "1e01e7f6",
            "jumpTo" : null,
            "answer": 1,
            "score" : 1,
            "position": "top"
        },
        {
            "id" : "c44552ad",
            "text" : [ "<span class=\"smGameTextTitleSize\">Validating HYPOTHESIS 3 (3/8)</span><p class=\"smGameTextSize\">In the northern part of the continent, civilizations such as Teotihuacan in Mexico were among the greatest of their time, with a population of around 100,000 people, making it the sixth largest city of its era (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('3fc02f8e-34be-455f-98f1-e0286e0f2767'); return false;\">INAH, <span class=\"htdate\"></span></a>):</p>", "<p class=\"desc\"><img id=\"imgMTeotihuacan\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgMTeotihuacan', '0%')\" src=\"images/Teotihuacan/TeotihuacanGeneral.jpg\" class=\"imgcenter\"/><b>Figure 4</b>: Overview of the city of Teotihuacan. Photo taken on <span class=\"htdate\"></span>, during a visit to the site.</p>" ],
            "desc": null,
            "next" : "a3cda068",
            "prev" : "920a393a",
            "jumpTo" : null,
            "answer": 1,
            "score" : 1,
            "position": "top"
        },
        {
            "id" : "a3cda068",
            "text" : [ "<span class=\"smGameTextTitleSize\">Validating HYPOTHESIS 3 (4/8)</span></p>", "<p><center><div class=\"first_steps_reflection_parent\"><div class=\"first_steps_reflection question_mark\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-brain\"></i></div><div class=\"first_steps_reflection\"><b>Reflection 1: On antiquity</b><br />How can we determine whether the buildings and artifacts are older than the first Europeans who reached America (<i>Abya Ayala</i>)?</div></div></center></p>" ],
            "desc": null,
            "next" : "0a573303",
            "prev" : "c44552ad",
            "jumpTo" : null,
            "answer": 1,
            "score" : 1,
            "position": "center"
        },
        {
            "id" : "0a573303",
            "text" : [ "<span class=\"smGameTextTitleSize\">Validating HYPOTHESIS 3 (5/8)</span><p class=\"smGameTextSize\">Our understanding of the atom has evolved significantly over time (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('424fb1ac-867e-4895-8a04-367655e6f1ea'); return false;\">Stewart, Ken, <span class=\"htdate\"></span></a> ; <a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('77a4d152-7328-47bb-bfea-1b1274649317'); return false;\">Rutherford, Ernest, <span class=\"htdate\"></span></a> ; <a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('35f9a553-247a-45dd-a756-65550d49f0ed'); return false;\">Schrödinger, Erwin, <span class=\"htdate\"></span></a> ; <a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('d4b0e3aa-954c-4bf3-b40f-6e6f62c854d5'); return false;\">History Tracers, <span class=\"htdate\"></span>, <i>Introduction to groups</i></a>):</p><p class=\"smGameTextSize\"><table><tr><th>Philosophical Atom</th><th>Niels Bohr's Atom</th><th>Quantum Atom</th></tr><tr><td><img id=\"imgAP\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgAP', '0%')\" src=\"images/HistoryTracers/Atom_Philosophical.png\" class=\"imgcenter\" /></td><td><img id=\"imgAB\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgAB', '0%')\" src=\"images/HistoryTracers/Atom_Bohr.png\"  class=\"imgcenter\"/></td><td><img id=\"imgAQ\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgAQ', '0%')\" src=\"images/HistoryTracers/Atom_Quantum.png\"  class=\"imgcenter\"/></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"3\" style=\"text-align: center; font-size: 70%;\"><b>Figura 5</b>: Simplified representation of the Hydrogen atom using different models. The source is available on the project's GitHub (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('240800f3-ede4-4deb-9d4e-915a3a03fa68'); return false;\">History Tracers, <span class=\"htdate\"></span></a>)</td></tr></table></p>", "<p class=\"smGameTextSize\">These advancements have enabled us to discover that Carbon atoms, found in living organisms such as plants and animals, undergo changes over time. This process allows us to date fossils up to 60,000 years old (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('b82b425f-c2c6-4173-97fa-64bd3eabc42d'); return false;\">Koppes, S., Lerner, L., <span class=\"htdate\"></span></a>). Consequently, when we find samples associated with these structures, we can estimate their age with reasonable accuracy.</p>" ],
            "desc": null,
            "next" : "f470f8ca",
            "prev" : "a3cda068",
            "jumpTo" : null,
            "answer": 1,
            "score" : 1,
            "position": "top"
        },
        {
            "id" : "f470f8ca",
            "text" : [ "<span class=\"smGameTextTitleSize\">Validating HYPOTHESIS 3 (6/8)</span><p class=\"smGameTextSize\">In addition to analyzing Carbon atoms, the discovery of human bones allows us to extract DNA for further study (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('24e35656-4e60-46b9-a4c4-08db2623336e'); return false;\">Pray, Leslie A., <span class=\"htdate\"></span></a> ; <a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('7b824b78-0249-403e-b2b5-d7b72878f1e3'); return false;\">Parreira, Daniel. <span class=\"htdate\"></span></a> ; <a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('195b1a2b-6c4c-44e4-aec6-9d9a8b60d758'); return false;\">El Robot de Platón. <span class=\"htdate\"></span></a> ; <a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('b30a6ec9-85c3-413e-a02f-b3eba83aa364'); return false;\">History Tracers. <span class=\"htdate\"></span></a>).</p>", "<p class=\"desc\"><img id=\"imgHS\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgHS', '0%')\" src=\"images/MexicoCityMuseo/HomoSapiens.jpg\" class=\"imgcenter\"/><b>Figure 6</b>: Photograph of a panel at the Museo Nacional de Antropología in Mexico City, Mexico (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('0be2ea18-ab78-4cb1-b3be-1ff0ba4ade95'); return false;\">Museo Nacional de Antropología</a>). The photo was taken during a visit to the museum on <span class=\"htdate\"></span>.</p>" ],
            "desc": null,
            "next" : "6ded6dec",
            "prev" : "0a573303",
            "jumpTo" : null,
            "answer": 1,
            "score" : 1,
            "position": "top"
        },
        {
            "id" : "6ded6dec",
            "text" : [ "<span class=\"smGameTextTitleSize\">Validating HYPOTHESIS 3 (7/8)</span><p class=\"smGameTextSize\">Genetic studies have confirmed José Acosta's proposal that humans migrated from Asia to the Americas (<i>Abya Ayala</i>) long before the arrival of Europeans on the continent (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillPrimarySource('c2f6de96-6589-4f66-858e-259bf3f3046a'); return false;\">Acosta, José, [ <span class=\"htdate\"></span>, (<span class=\"htdate\"></span>)], pp. 240</a> ; <a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('601750ac-2b5b-4353-bd52-74a9c8483808'); return false;\">O’Rourke, Dennis H., and Jennifer A. Raff., <span class=\"htdate\"></span></a> ; <a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('064c3691-1f4c-491b-b643-150c011b4525'); return false;\">Goebel, Ted, et al., <span class=\"htdate\"></span></a> ; <a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('3aded71f-8528-4d70-97fc-295b04ca5ebe'); return false;\">Pirula, <span class=\"htdate\"></span></a> ; <a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('6af790a8-2fe4-417d-9bc9-615cd5be4398'); return false;\">Pirula, <span class=\"htdate\"></span></a> ; <a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('98456252-713f-403d-81bb-462f753d3979'); return false;\">Iamarino, Atila, <span class=\"htdate\"></span></a> ; <a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('4eafd7e9-cfe7-47b3-888a-6afa2870637a'); return false;\">Moras, Roberto, <span class=\"htdate\"></span></a>).</p>", "<p class=\"desc\"><img id=\"imgBering\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgBering', '0%')\" src=\"images/ElSalvadorMuseo/Bering.jpg\" class=\"imgcenter\"/><b>Figure 7</b>: A section of a map illustrating the migration of Indigenous peoples across the Bering Strait. The photograph was taken at the Museo Nacional de Antropología in San Salvador, El Salvador (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('0be2ea18-ab78-4cb1-b3be-1ff0ba4ade95'); return false;\">Museo Nacional de Antropología</a>), during a visit on <span class=\"htdate\"></span>." ],
            "desc": null,
